-## Supervisor Acceptance Checklist
-
-A supervisor repair proposal is acceptable only when all of these are true:
-
-- It changes daemon supervision, retry guidance, prompt guidance, preflight diagnostics, focused daemon tests, or the task board.
-- It does not complete the stalled public PDF extraction fixture task itself.
-- It keeps the file set smaller than the repeated failed proposals unless the daemon code itself must be replaced.
-- It preserves completed task-board checkboxes and does not mark domain work complete by documentation alone.
-- It uses fixture-first and validation-first instructions before any live or authenticated automation.
-- It creates no private DevHub artifacts, raw crawl output, downloaded documents, auth state, traces, or session files.
